This paper discusses the cognitive processes involved in design with reuse and software documenting, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also emphasizes the importance of natural language documentation, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper discusses the manipulation of cognitive entities during design, which is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses cognitive models of text processing, which is relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
